#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn22.84"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn22.84:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 22 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 22 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.84:0.2"
msgid "9. Theravagga "
msgstr "9. Senior Mendicants "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn22.84:0.3"
msgid "84. Tissasutta "
msgstr "84. With Tissa "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "sn22.84:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthinidānaṃ. "
msgstr "At Sāvatthī. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.84:1.2"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena āyasmā tisso bhagavato pitucchāputto sambahulānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ evamāroceti: "
msgstr "Now at that time Venerable Tissa, the Buddha’s paternal cousin, informed several mendicants: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.84:1.3"
msgid "“api me, āvuso, madhurakajāto viya kāyo; "
msgstr "“Reverends, my body feels like it’s drugged. I’m disorientated, the teachings don’t inspire me, and dullness and drowsiness fill my mind. I live the spiritual life dissatisfied, and have doubts about the teachings.” "

msgctxt "sn22.84:1.4"
msgid "disāpi me na pakkhāyanti; "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn22.84:1.5"
msgid "dhammāpi maṃ na paṭibhanti; "
msgstr " "

#. VAR: thinamiddhañca → thīnamiddhañca (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "sn22.84:1.6"
msgid "thinamiddhañca me cittaṃ pariyādāya tiṭṭhati; "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn22.84:1.7"
msgid "anabhirato ca brahmacariyaṃ carāmi; "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn22.84:1.8"
msgid "hoti ca me dhammesu vicikicchā”ti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "sn22.84:2.1"
msgid "Atha kho sambahulā bhikkhū yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu. Ekamantaṃ nisinnā kho te bhikkhū bhagavantaṃ etadavocuṃ: "
msgstr "Then several mendicants went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and told him what had happened. "

msgctxt "sn22.84:2.2"
msgid "“āyasmā, bhante, tisso bhagavato pitucchāputto sambahulānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ evamāroceti: "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn22.84:2.3"
msgid "‘api me, āvuso, madhurakajāto viya kāyo; "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn22.84:2.4"
msgid "disāpi me na pakkhāyanti; "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn22.84:2.5"
msgid "dhammāpi maṃ na paṭibhanti; "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn22.84:2.6"
msgid "thinamiddhañca me cittaṃ pariyādāya tiṭṭhati; "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn22.84:2.7"
msgid "anabhirato ca brahmacariyaṃ carāmi; "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn22.84:2.8"
msgid "hoti ca me dhammesu vicikicchā’”ti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.107, sc3
msgctxt "sn22.84:3.1"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā aññataraṃ bhikkhuṃ āmantesi: "
msgstr "So the Buddha said to a certain monk, "

# NOTE: PTS has the usual satthā taṃ, āvuso sāriputta, āmanteti, which is presumably omitted by mistake in MS.
msgctxt "sn22.84:3.2"
msgid "“ehi tvaṃ, bhikkhu, mama vacanena tissaṃ bhikkhuṃ āmantehī”ti. "
msgstr "“Please, mendicant, in my name tell the mendicant Tissa that the Teacher summons him.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.84:3.3"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho so bhikkhu bhagavato paṭissutvā yenāyasmā tisso tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ tissaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "“Yes, sir,” that monk replied. He went to Tissa and said to him, "

msgctxt "sn22.84:3.4"
msgid "“satthā taṃ, āvuso tissa, āmantetī”ti. "
msgstr "“Reverend Tissa, the teacher summons you.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.84:3.5"
msgid "“Evamāvuso”ti kho āyasmā tisso tassa bhikkhuno paṭissutvā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho āyasmantaṃ tissaṃ bhagavā etadavoca: "
msgstr "“Yes, reverend,” Tissa replied. He went to the Buddha, bowed, and sat down to one side. The Buddha said to him: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.84:3.6"
msgid "“saccaṃ kira tvaṃ, tissa, sambahulānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ evamārocesi: "
msgstr "“Is it really true, Tissa, that you informed several mendicants that "

msgctxt "sn22.84:3.7"
msgid "‘api me, āvuso, madhurakajāto viya kāyo … pe … "
msgstr "your body feels like it’s drugged … "

msgctxt "sn22.84:3.8"
msgid "hoti ca me dhammesu vicikicchā’”ti? "
msgstr "and you have doubts about the teachings?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.84:3.9"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”. "
msgstr "“Yes, sir.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.84:3.10"
msgid "“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, tissa, "
msgstr "“What do you think, Tissa? "

msgctxt "sn22.84:3.11"
msgid "rūpe avigatarāgassa avigatacchandassa avigatapemassa avigatapipāsassa avigatapariḷāhassa avigatataṇhassa, tassa rūpassa vipariṇāmaññathābhāvā uppajjanti sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsā”ti? "
msgstr "If you’re not rid of greed, desire, fondness, thirst, passion, and craving for form, when that form decays and perishes, will it give rise to sorrow, lamentation, pain, sadness, and distress?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.84:3.12"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”. "
msgstr "“Yes, sir.” "

# NOTE: The Buddha’s incredible skill in teaching …
#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "sn22.84:4.1"
msgid "“Sādhu sādhu, tissa. "
msgstr "“Good, good, Tissa! "

msgctxt "sn22.84:4.2"
msgid "Evañhetaṃ, tissa, hoti. "
msgstr "That’s how it is, Tissa, "

msgctxt "sn22.84:4.3"
msgid "Yathā taṃ rūpe avigatarāgassa … "
msgstr "when you’re not rid of greed for form. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.84:4.4"
msgid "vedanāya … "
msgstr "If you’re not rid of greed for feeling … "

msgctxt "sn22.84:4.5"
msgid "saññāya … "
msgstr "perception … "

msgctxt "sn22.84:4.6"
msgid "saṅkhāresu avigatarāgassa … pe … "
msgstr "choices … "

msgctxt "sn22.84:4.7"
msgid "tesaṃ saṅkhārānaṃ vipariṇāmaññathābhāvā uppajjanti sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsā”ti? "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn22.84:4.8"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”. "
msgstr " "

#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "sn22.84:5.1"
msgid "“Sādhu sādhu, tissa. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn22.84:5.2"
msgid "Evañhetaṃ, tissa, hoti. "
msgstr " "

# NOTE: An obvious typo here in anigata
msgctxt "sn22.84:5.3"
msgid "Yathā taṃ saṅkhāresu anigatarāgassa, viññāṇe avigatarāgassa avigatacchandassa avigatapemassa avigatapipāsassa avigatapariḷāhassa avigatataṇhassa, tassa viññāṇassa vipariṇāmaññathābhāvā uppajjanti sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsā”ti? "
msgstr "consciousness, when that consciousness decays and perishes, will it give rise to sorrow, lamentation, pain, sadness, and distress?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.84:5.4"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”. "
msgstr "“Yes, sir.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "sn22.84:6.1"
msgid "“Sādhu sādhu, tissa. "
msgstr "“Good, good, Tissa! "

msgctxt "sn22.84:6.2"
msgid "Evañhetaṃ, tissa, hoti. "
msgstr "That’s how it is, Tissa, "

msgctxt "sn22.84:6.3"
msgid "Yathā taṃ viññāṇe avigatarāgassa. "
msgstr "when you’re not rid of greed for consciousness. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.84:6.4"
msgid "Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, tissa, "
msgstr "What do you think, Tissa? "

msgctxt "sn22.84:6.5"
msgid "rūpe vigatarāgassa vigatacchandassa vigatapemassa vigatapipāsassa vigatapariḷāhassa vigatataṇhassa, tassa rūpassa vipariṇāmaññathābhāvā uppajjanti sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsā”ti? "
msgstr "If you are rid of greed, desire, fondness, thirst, passion, and craving for form, when that form decays and perishes, will it give rise to sorrow, lamentation, pain, sadness, and distress?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.84:6.6"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”. "
msgstr "“No, sir.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.108, sc7
msgctxt "sn22.84:7.1"
msgid "“Sādhu sādhu, tissa. "
msgstr "“Good, good, Tissa! "

msgctxt "sn22.84:7.2"
msgid "Evañhetaṃ, tissa, hoti. "
msgstr "That’s how it is, Tissa, "

msgctxt "sn22.84:7.3"
msgid "Yathā taṃ rūpe vigatarāgassa … "
msgstr "when you are rid of greed for form … "

msgctxt "sn22.84:7.4"
msgid "vedanāya … "
msgstr "feeling … "

msgctxt "sn22.84:7.5"
msgid "saññāya … "
msgstr "perception … "

msgctxt "sn22.84:7.6"
msgid "saṅkhāresu vigatarāgassa … "
msgstr "choices … "

msgctxt "sn22.84:7.7"
msgid "viññāṇe vigatarāgassa vigatacchandassa vigatapemassa vigatapipāsassa vigatapariḷāhassa vigatataṇhassa tassa viññāṇassa vipariṇāmaññathābhāvā uppajjanti sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsā”ti? "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn22.84:7.8"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”. "
msgstr " "

#. REF: sc8
msgctxt "sn22.84:8.1"
msgid "“Sādhu sādhu, tissa. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn22.84:8.2"
msgid "Evañhetaṃ, tissa, hoti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn22.84:8.3"
msgid "Yathā taṃ viññāṇe vigatarāgassa. "
msgstr "consciousness. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.84:8.4"
msgid "Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, tissa, "
msgstr "What do you think, Tissa? "

msgctxt "sn22.84:8.5"
msgid "rūpaṃ niccaṃ vā aniccaṃ vā”ti? "
msgstr "Is form permanent or impermanent?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.84:8.6"
msgid "“Aniccaṃ, bhante”. "
msgstr "“Impermanent, sir.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.84:8.7"
msgid "“Vedanā … "
msgstr "“Is feeling … "

msgctxt "sn22.84:8.8"
msgid "saññā … "
msgstr "perception … "

msgctxt "sn22.84:8.9"
msgid "saṅkhārā … "
msgstr "choices … "

msgctxt "sn22.84:8.10"
msgid "viññāṇaṃ niccaṃ vā aniccaṃ vā”ti? "
msgstr "consciousness permanent or impermanent?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.84:8.11"
msgid "“Aniccaṃ, bhante”. "
msgstr "“Impermanent, sir.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.84:8.12"
msgid "“Tasmātiha … pe … "
msgstr "“So you should truly see … "

msgctxt "sn22.84:8.13"
msgid "evaṃ passaṃ … pe … "
msgstr "Seeing this … "

msgctxt "sn22.84:8.14"
msgid "nāparaṃ itthattāyāti pajānāti. "
msgstr "They understand: ‘… there is no return to any state of existence.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc9
msgctxt "sn22.84:9.1"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, tissa, dve purisā—"
msgstr "Suppose, Tissa, there were two people. "

msgctxt "sn22.84:9.2"
msgid "eko puriso amaggakusalo, eko puriso maggakusalo. "
msgstr "One was not skilled in the path, the other was. "

msgctxt "sn22.84:9.3"
msgid "Tamenaṃ so amaggakusalo puriso amuṃ maggakusalaṃ purisaṃ maggaṃ puccheyya. "
msgstr "The one not skilled in the path would question the one skilled in the path, "

msgctxt "sn22.84:9.4"
msgid "So evaṃ vadeyya: "
msgstr "who would reply: "

msgctxt "sn22.84:9.5"
msgid "‘ehi, bho purisa, ayaṃ maggo. "
msgstr "‘Come, good man, this is the path. "

msgctxt "sn22.84:9.6"
msgid "Tena muhuttaṃ gaccha. "
msgstr "Go down it a little, "

# NOTE: Interesting use of muncati and ganhati.
msgctxt "sn22.84:9.7"
msgid "Tena muhuttaṃ gantvā dakkhissasi dvedhāpathaṃ, tattha vāmaṃ muñcitvā dakkhiṇaṃ gaṇhāhi. "
msgstr "and you’ll see a fork in the road. Ignore the left, and take the right-hand path. "

msgctxt "sn22.84:9.8"
msgid "Tena muhuttaṃ gaccha. "
msgstr "Go a little further, "

msgctxt "sn22.84:9.9"
msgid "Tena muhuttaṃ gantvā dakkhissasi tibbaṃ vanasaṇḍaṃ. "
msgstr "and you’ll see a dark forest grove. "

msgctxt "sn22.84:9.10"
msgid "Tena muhuttaṃ gaccha. "
msgstr "Go a little further, "

msgctxt "sn22.84:9.11"
msgid "Tena muhuttaṃ gantvā dakkhissasi mahantaṃ ninnaṃ pallalaṃ. "
msgstr "and you’ll see an expanse of low-lying marshes. "

msgctxt "sn22.84:9.12"
msgid "Tena muhuttaṃ gaccha. "
msgstr "Go a little further, "

msgctxt "sn22.84:9.13"
msgid "Tena muhuttaṃ gantvā dakkhissasi sobbhaṃ papātaṃ. "
msgstr "and you’ll see a large, steep cliff. "

msgctxt "sn22.84:9.14"
msgid "Tena muhuttaṃ gaccha. "
msgstr "Go a little further, "

msgctxt "sn22.84:9.15"
msgid "Tena muhuttaṃ gantvā dakkhissasi samaṃ bhūmibhāgaṃ ramaṇīyan’ti. "
msgstr "and you’ll see level, cleared parkland.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.109, sc10
msgctxt "sn22.84:10.1"
msgid "Upamā kho myāyaṃ, tissa, katā atthassa viññāpanāya. "
msgstr "I’ve made up this simile to make a point. "

msgctxt "sn22.84:10.2"
msgid "Ayaṃ cevettha attho: "
msgstr "And this is what it means. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.84:10.3"
msgid "‘puriso amaggakusalo’ti kho, tissa, puthujjanassetaṃ adhivacanaṃ. "
msgstr "‘A person who is not skilled in the path’ is a term for an ordinary uneducated person. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.84:10.4"
msgid "‘Puriso maggakusalo’ti kho, tissa, tathāgatassetaṃ adhivacanaṃ arahato sammāsambuddhassa. "
msgstr "‘A person who is skilled in the path’ is a term for the Realized One, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.84:10.5"
msgid "‘Dvedhāpatho’ti kho, tissa, vicikicchāyetaṃ adhivacanaṃ. "
msgstr "‘A fork in the road’ is a term for doubt. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.84:10.6"
msgid "‘Vāmo maggo’ti kho, tissa, aṭṭhaṅgikassetaṃ micchāmaggassa adhivacanaṃ, seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr "‘The left-hand path’ is a term for the wrong eightfold path, that is, "

msgctxt "sn22.84:10.7"
msgid "micchādiṭṭhiyā … pe … micchāsamādhissa. "
msgstr "wrong view … wrong immersion. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.84:10.8"
msgid "‘Dakkhiṇo maggo’ti kho, tissa, ariyassetaṃ aṭṭhaṅgikassa maggassa adhivacanaṃ, seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr "‘The right-hand path’ is a term for the noble eightfold path, that is, "

msgctxt "sn22.84:10.9"
msgid "sammādiṭṭhiyā … pe … sammāsamādhissa. "
msgstr "right view … right immersion. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.84:10.10"
msgid "‘Tibbo vanasaṇḍo’ti kho, tissa, avijjāyetaṃ adhivacanaṃ. "
msgstr "‘A dark forest grove’ is a term for ignorance. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.84:10.11"
msgid "‘Mahantaṃ ninnaṃ pallalan’ti kho, tissa, kāmānametaṃ adhivacanaṃ. "
msgstr "‘An expanse of low-lying marshes’ is a term for sensual pleasures. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.84:10.12"
msgid "‘Sobbho papāto’ti kho, tissa, kodhūpāyāsassetaṃ adhivacanaṃ. "
msgstr "‘A large, steep cliff’ is a term for anger and distress. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.84:10.13"
msgid "‘Samo bhūmibhāgo ramaṇīyo’ti kho, tissa, nibbānassetaṃ adhivacanaṃ. "
msgstr "‘Level, cleared parkland’ is a term for extinguishment. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.84:10.14"
msgid "Abhirama, tissa, abhirama, tissa. "
msgstr "Rejoice, Tissa, rejoice! "

# NOTE: Wow, that’s a major variant. It looks very much like a commentarial gloss.
#. VAR: Ahamovādena ahamanuggahena ahamanusāsaniyā”ti → ahamāmisadhammānuggahena mamovādena mamānusāsaniyāti (mr)
msgctxt "sn22.84:10.15"
msgid "Ahamovādena ahamanuggahena ahamanusāsaniyā”ti. "
msgstr "I’m here to advise you, to support you, and to teach you.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc11
msgctxt "sn22.84:11.1"
msgid "Idamavoca bhagavā. "
msgstr "That is what the Buddha said. "

msgctxt "sn22.84:11.2"
msgid "Attamano āyasmā tisso bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinandīti. "
msgstr "Satisfied, Venerable Tissa was happy with what the Buddha said. "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn22.84:11.3"
msgid "Dutiyaṃ. "
msgstr ""

